CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 20, 1960, pg. B10 reads: "Chi Delta Mu Fraternity Entertains Lavishly - Dr. Charles Burks, Mrs. Burks, third and fourth from right, and guests" Portion of accompanying article published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 20, 1960, pg. A7 by Toki Schalk Johnson reads:"Wednesday brought forth the annual dinner dance given by the Chi Delta Mu Fraternity in beautifully decorated New Arena."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of five men, including Dr. Charles Burks fourth from right, and four women, including Mrs. Burks, third from right, seated at rectangular banquet table for Chi Delta Mu supper dance in New Arena Supper Club
